   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "62baab9d",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "**Trade-off:** the vanilla RNN is smallest and fastest but least accurate. The LSTM adds gating (~4× the recurrent parameters) and gains a large accuracy jump. The BRNN doubles LSTM cost again for a smaller incremental gain — useful when both past and future context matter."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "9b09952c",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "### 4.2 Live prediction"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "id": "19a15557",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "def predict_sentiment(text, model, vocab, device):\n",
    "    model.eval()\n",
    "    with torch.no_grad():\n",
    "        ids     = encode(text)\n",
    "        tensor  = torch.tensor(ids, dtype=torch.long).unsqueeze(0).to(device)\n",
    "        lengths = torch.tensor([len(ids)], dtype=torch.long)\n",
    "        probs   = torch.softmax(model(tensor, lengths), dim=1).squeeze(0)\n",
    "        pred    = int(probs.argmax().item())\n",
    "    return (\"Positive\" if pred == 1 else \"Negative\"), float(probs[pred].item())\n",
    "\n",
    "test_reviews = [\n",
    "    \"This film was absolutely wonderful. The acting was superb and I loved every minute.\",\n",
    "    \"One of the best movies I have ever seen. Highly recommend to everyone!\",\n",
    "    \"I'm not sure how I feel about this. Some parts were good, others not so much.\",\n",
    "    \"It wasn't terrible but I wouldn't watch it again. The plot made no sense at times.\",\n",
    "]\n",
    "for review in test_reviews:\n",
    "    label, conf = predict_sentiment(review, model_brnn, vocab, device)\n",
    "    print(f\"[{label} ({conf:.2%})] — {review[:80]}...\")"
   ]
  },
